headlines.description: — The challenge to Jayson Tatum against a Brooklyn lineup that featured a rare appearance from both Kevin Durant and Kyrie Irving: “Take the alpha approach.”
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum's 54 leads Celtics past Durant, Irving, Nets 126-120

headlines.description: — Khris Middleton and Jrue Holiday made sure the Milwaukee Bucks withstood Giannis Antetokounmpo’s foul trouble and got through arguably the toughest three-game stretch of their schedule unscathed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Khris Middleton scores 44 points, Bucks rally to beat Suns

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis finally made his debut for the Washington Wizards — and didn't need much time to make a big impact.
headlines.shortLinkText: In Wizards debut, Porzingis keys 133-123 win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Kevin Porter Jr. scored 29 points, Christian Wood added 28 points and 13 rebounds and the Houston Rockets beat the Memphis Grizzlies 123-112 on Sunday night to end a 12-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets beat Grizzlies 123-112 to end 12-game losing streak

events.name: Utah Jazz at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic said making a Utah Jazz franchise-record 11 3-pointers wasn't all that complicated.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bogdanovic hits 11 3-pointers as Jazz defeat Thunder 116-103

headlines.description: — The Cavaliers couldn't even celebrate a signature win. They've got another significant injury to overcome.
headlines.shortLinkText: All-Star Allen injured during Cavs' 104-96 win over Raptors

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — The Denver Nuggets lost their big lead, head coach and cool.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Nuggets regroup to beat Pelicans 138-130 in OT

events.name: New York Knicks at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett had 24 points and nine rebounds and the Knicks dominated the Los Angeles Clippers in a 116-93 victory Sunday night that snapped New York’s seven-game losing skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks dominate Clippers 116-93 to snap 7-game skid
